{
  "texts": [
    "One such meta-classifier is the CostSensitiveClassifier (Trigg 2023a), which enables users to transform a base classifier in Weka into a cost-sensitive model by incorporating a cost matrix during model training.",
    "The cost matrix can be conveniently specified as input, facilitating the automatic handling of class imbalance.",
    "Another available meta-classifier is MetaCost (Trigg 2023b).",
    "The open-source programming language R (2023) appeared prominently in 9 papers (5.2%) within the selected studies, owing to its extensive collection of packages designed for ML and statistical modelling.",
    "R offers a wide range of packages that support CSL."
  ]
}